rComments: I would say she's a really caring and internationally-friendly prof (she said she will make her test lest heavier in coming up terms), and if you put in some time to work with your study group, you would definetely pass. But if you are thinking of an easy-A, I don't think that's possible for any courses in our school.

Have to say she is a nice professor. But her midterm was hard and give lower marks than you expected in other assignments. If you just wanna learn something you can definitely choose her, she will prepare weekly discussions and you can check your learning process from that. If you wanna a higher grade, then just choose another prof will be better.
